<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4664.3.9>
    bibo:endPage "433" ;
    bibo:issue "3" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2019-09-04" ;
    bibo:startPage "423" ;
    bibo:volume "4664" ;
    dc:creator "Vega, Rocio; Razzolini, Emanuel; Arbetman, Marina; Viozzi, Gustavo" ;
    dc:date "2019" ;
    dc:title "Two new species of Gyrodactylus von Nordmann, 1832 (Monogenoidea: Gyrodactylidae) parasitizing introduced poeciliids in Patagonia" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3385623>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3385625>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3385627>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3385629> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3385623>
    dc:description "FIGURES 6–10. Gyrodactylus breviradix n. sp. 6. Whole specimen. 7. Haptor. 8. Marginal hook. 9. Male copulatory organs. 10. Anchor." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3385623/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3385625>
    dc:description "FIGURES 11–12. Comparison of marginal hook hooklets among the two new species from Patagonia Argentina (solid line) and the most similar neotropical Gyrodactylus especies (broken line). 11. Gyrodactylus decemmaculati n. sp. and the overlapping hooklets. 12. Gyrodactylus breviradix n. sp. and the overlapping hooklets." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3385625/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3385627>
    dc:description "FIGURE 13. Maximum Likelihood method based on the Tamura-Nei model. The tree with the highest log likelihood (- 3376.1634) is shown and distances were estimated using the Maximum Composite Likelihood (MCL) approach, and then selecting the topology with superior log likelihood value. Branch lengths are measured as the number of substitutions per site. The analysis involved 25 nucleotide sequences." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3385627/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3385629>
    dc:description "FIGURE 14. Blue line: Distribution of pairwise distance comparisons within species of gyrodactylids (without putative new ones) and between species (red line). Black dots represent de pairwise distance of newly proposed species (intraspecific), and green dots represent the pairwise comparisons of putative species with other gyrodactylids (interespecific)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3385629/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

